title: Hungary Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Hungary Three Month Interbank Rate was at 16.39 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in Hungary averaged 7.96 percent from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 32 percent in September of 1995 and a record low of 0.02 percent in January of 2018. In Hungary, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Hungary Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bank of Hungary
